# EasyEffects
#
# Enabled Features (Audio Processing Modules):
# - calf: Enables the Calf Studio Gear suite (provides the Limiter).
# - zamaudio: Enables ZamAudio plugins (provides the Maximizer).
media-sound/easyeffects calf zamaudio

# Audacity
#
# media-sound/audacity:
# - id3tag: Enables ID3 metadata tagging (Artist, Track, Album) for MP3 exports.
#   Required to prevent blank metadata fields in exported audio files.
# - sbsms: Provides a high-quality algorithm for time-stretching and
#   pitch-shifting. Recommended for audio manipulation beyond basic splicing.
media-sound/audacity id3tag sbsms

# PulseEffects
#
# Enabled Features (Audio Processing Modules):
# - calf: Enables the Calf Studio Gear suite (provides the Limiter).
# - zamaudio: Enables ZamAudio plugins (provides the Maximizer).
# - lsp: Provides high-quality parametric equalizers, multiband compressors, and
#   alternative limiters. Required for most community presets to function.
# - rnnoise: Enables a recurrent neural network noise reduction plugin. Filters
#   background noise and keyboard typing without distorting the human voice.
# - bs2b: Bauer stereophonic-to-binaural. Simulates a speaker crossfeed to
#   reduce listening fatigue when using headphones.
media-sound/pulseeffects calf zamaudio

# PulseEffect and EasyEffects dependencies
#
# Disabled Features (Build Optimizations & UI Stripping):
# - calf (-gui): Disables standalone graphical interfaces. The intent is to host
#   these plugins exclusively inside PulseEffects.
# - lsp-plugins (-X): Disables X11 UI binaries to save compilation overhead.
#   PulseEffects manages the plugin parameters natively.
# - zam-plugins (-opengl): Disables OpenGL, which ZamAudio uses exclusively for
#   its standalone UI binaries.
# - serd (-tools): Disables standalone command-line utilities (e.g., serdi) used
#   by developers for RDF validation in the terminal.
media-plugins/calf -gui lv2
media-libs/lsp-plugins -X
dev-libs/serd -tools
media-plugins/zam-plugins -opengl

# OBS Studio
#
# browser: Enables CEF (Chromium Embedded Framework) for web-based overlays.
#          Flags configuration analysis for disabled media-video/obs-studio
#          options:
# fdk: Enables the Fraunhofer FDK AAC encoder. It offers excellent audio quality
#      but operates under a restrictive license. Default AAC encoders are
#      generally sufficient.
# jack: Enables the JACK Audio Connection Kit backend. Highly effective for
#       low-latency audio engineering, but unnecessary when PipeWire handles
#       your system audio routing.
# lua: Enables Lua scripting. Disabling this is highly recommended, allowing
#      you to centralize your custom OBS automation entirely in Python. mpegts
# python: Enables Python scripting support. You should remove the minus sign to
#         enable this flag, providing a familiar and native Python environment
#         for building scene switchers and custom tooling.
# qsv: Enables Intel Quick Sync Video.
# websocket: Enables the obs-websocket plugin for remote control.
# vlc: Adds the VLC video source for advanced media handling. The vlc flag
#      enables the VLC Video Source, offering advanced media handling
#      compared to the default FFmpeg source. It introduces support for
#      multi-file playlists, directory looping, and superior buffering
#      for external network streams like RTSP or RTMP. Furthermore, it
#      provides better compatibility with obscure video formats, embedded
#      subtitles, and multiple audio tracks. While it is unnecessary for
#      basic single-file playback, it is highly recommended for complex
#      scenes and remote feed integration.
media-video/obs-studio python lua
